        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 2:04PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 204 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles southeast of Blowing Rock, or near Blowing Rock In Caldwell
County, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Blowing Rock In Caldwell County, Globe, and Upton.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
